Hi, @sp74fg2! It has been nearly a month after my reply, and since that I thought maybe I could try to extend the data myself, so yeah, I've done it. The improved data lives in new repository (db.trakt.extended-anitrakt) as the final output schema is not backward compatible with old one. It features mappings from IMDb, TMDB, TVDB, TVRage and Letterboxd through
interesting
way I'd say. Since I iterate it myself, I found a lot of invalids, which you may be interested to lookup and fix it on your end. Check it on ignore_movies.json, ignore_tv.json, not_exist_movies_ex.json, and not_exist_tv_ex.json. For split cour, I have hard time to think how to put it as well, not just MAL S2 != Trakt S2, but it can be MAL E1 == TMDB/Trakt E1-E2 as well So a simple boolean is enough I guess? So people (or dev specifically) have informed decision to handle it in their own way. For this usecase, i decided to implement is_split_cour KV and will nullify season info. I don't implement episode offset because that'd be super tiring, arguably.

On a rainy day, Fuji meets a cute critter posing as a dog and offering an umbrella and a cue card that says, Please take me home and she cant resist. With this dog-posters quirky charm and mysterious ways, life together becomes a heartwarming adventure of friendship and shared seasons.
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Drama, Music, Romance, Slice of Life

Piano prodigy Arima Kousei dominated the competition and all child musicians knew his name. But after his mother, who was also his instructor, passed away, he had a mental breakdown while performing at a recital. This resulted in him no longer being able to hear the sound of his piano playing. Two years later, Kousei hasnt touched the piano and views the world without any flair or color. He was content at living out his life with his good friends Tsubaki and Watari until, one day, a girl changed everything. Miyazono Kaori is a pretty, free spirited violinist whose playing style reflects her personality. Kaori helps Kousei return to the music world and show that it should be free and mold breaking unlike the structured and rigid style Kousei was used to.

At a speed-dating event, Taika hits it off with a woman named Ayano, a doctor who's eager to have children. However, just as the matching couples are about to be announced, he panics and makes a break for it when his fears about his erectile dysfunction begin to surface... Later, at an appointment for his condition, Taika is shocked to discover that his doctor is none other than Ayano herself! On top of that, he realizes that when he's with Ayano, his erectile dysfunction disappears! (Source: OceanVeil) Note: Episode 1 receives an advanced distribution on AnimeFesta on June 13th, 2025. The start date reflects the start of the regular series broadcasting.

The second season of Grand Blue. University is back in session for Iori, and so are the booze-fueled parties! Between diving club shenanigans, a surprise from his sister, and wild tests of courage, normal college life is anything but. Dive back into the madness with Iori and his beloved crew of lively splash artists. (Source: Crunchyroll)
